tool_description: Get data around Pokemon and the Pokemon universe.
name: Poke
title: Poke

api_list.name: getAbilityByName
api_list.description: Abilities provide passive effects for Pokémon in battle or in the overworld. Pokémon have multiple possible abilities but can have only one ability at a time.

required_parameters.name: abilityName
required_parameters.description: Id or name of the ability

api_list.name: getBerryByName
api_list.description: Returns information about berry

required_parameters.name: berryName
required_parameters.description: Id or name of the berry

api_list.name: getBerryFirmnessByName
api_list.description: Returns information about berries with provided firmness

required_parameters.name: berryFirmness
required_parameters.description: Id or name of the berry firmness

api_list.name: getBerryFlavorByName
api_list.description: Returns information about berries with provided flavor

required_parameters.name: berryFlavor
required_parameters.description: Id or name of the berry flavor

api_list.name: getCharacteristicById
api_list.description: Characteristics indicate which stat contains a Pokémon's highest IV. A Pokémon's Characteristic is determined by the remainder of its highest IV divided by 5 (gene_modulo).

required_parameters.name: characteristicId
required_parameters.description: Id of the characteristic

api_list.name: getContestEffectById
api_list.description: Returns contest effect according to provided Id

required_parameters.name: contestId
required_parameters.description: Id of the contest type

api_list.name: getContestTypeByName
api_list.description: Contest types are categories judges used to weigh a Pokémon's condition in Pokémon contests.

required_parameters.name: contestName
required_parameters.description: Id or name of contest type

api_list.name: getEggGroupByName
api_list.description: Egg Groups are categories which determine which Pokémon are able to interbreed. Pokémon may belong to either one or two Egg Groups.

required_parameters.name: eggGroupName
required_parameters.description: Id or name of the egg group

api_list.name: getEncounterConditionByName
api_list.description: Conditions which affect what pokemon might appear in the wild, e.g., day or night.

required_parameters.name: conditionName
required_parameters.description: Id or name of the condition

api_list.name: getEncounterConditionValueByName
api_list.description: Encounter condition values are the various states that an encounter condition can have, i.e., time of day can be either day or night.

required_parameters.name: conditionValueName
required_parameters.description: Id or name of the condition value

api_list.name: getEncounterMethodByName
api_list.description: Methods by which the player might can encounter Pokémon in the wild, e.g., walking in tall grass.

required_parameters.name: methodName
required_parameters.description: Id or name of the method

api_list.name: getEvolutionChainById
api_list.description: Evolution chains are essentially family trees. They start with the lowest stage within a family and detail evolution conditions for each as well as Pokémon they can evolve into up through the hierarchy.

required_parameters.name: chainId
required_parameters.description: Id of the evolution chain

api_list.name: getEvolutionTriggerByName
api_list.description: Evolution triggers are the events and conditions that cause a Pokémon to evolve.

required_parameters.name: triggerName
required_parameters.description: Id or name of the evolution trigger

api_list.name: getGenderByName
api_list.description: Genders were introduced in Generation II for the purposes of breeding Pokémon but can also result in visual differences or even different evolutionary lines.

required_parameters.name: genderName
required_parameters.description: Id or name of the gender

api_list.name: getGenerationByName
api_list.description: A generation is a grouping of the Pokémon games that separates them based on the Pokémon they include. In each generation, a new set of Pokémon, Moves, Abilities and Types that did not exist in the previous generation are released.

required_parameters.name: generationName
required_parameters.description: Id or name of the generation

api_list.name: getGrowthRateByName
api_list.description: Growth rates are the speed with which Pokémon gain levels through experience.

required_parameters.name: growthRateName
required_parameters.description: Id or name of the growth rate

api_list.name: getItemAttributeByName
api_list.description: Item attributes define particular aspects of items, e.g. "usable in battle" or "consumable".

required_parameters.name: itemAttributeName
required_parameters.description: Id or name of the item attribute

api_list.name: getItemByName
api_list.description: An item is an object in the games which the player can pick up, keep in their bag, and use in some manner. They have various uses, including healing, powering up, helping catch Pokémon, or to access a new area.

required_parameters.name: itemName
required_parameters.description: Id or name of the item

api_list.name: getItemCategoryByName
api_list.description: Item categories determine where items will be placed in the players bag.

required_parameters.name: itemCategoryName
required_parameters.description: Id or name of the item category

api_list.name: getItemFlingEffectByName
api_list.description: Item categories determine where items will be placed in the players bag.

required_parameters.name: itemFlingEffectName
required_parameters.description: Id or name of the item fling effect

api_list.name: getItemPocketByName
api_list.description: Pockets within the players bag used for storing items by category.

required_parameters.name: itemPocketName
required_parameters.description: Id or name of the item pocket

api_list.name: getLanguageByName
api_list.description: Languages for translations of API resource information.

required_parameters.name: languageName
required_parameters.description: Id or name of the language

api_list.name: getLocationAreaByName
api_list.description: Location areas are sections of areas, such as floors in a building or cave. Each area has its own set of possible Pokémon encounters.

required_parameters.name: locationAreaName
required_parameters.description: Id or name of the location area

api_list.name: getLocationByName
api_list.description: Locations that can be visited within the games. Locations make up sizable portions of regions, like cities or routes.

required_parameters.name: locationName
required_parameters.description: Id or name of the location

api_list.name: getMachineById
api_list.description: Machines are the representation of items that teach moves to Pokémon. They vary from version to version, so it is not certain that one specific TM or HM corresponds to a single Machine.

required_parameters.name: machineId
required_parameters.description: Id of the machine

api_list.name: getMoveAilmentByName
api_list.description: Move Ailments are status conditions caused by moves used during battle.

required_parameters.name: moveAilmentName
required_parameters.description: Id or name of the move ailment

api_list.name: getMoveBattleStyleByName
api_list.description: Styles of moves when used in the Battle Palace.

required_parameters.name: moveBattleStyleName
required_parameters.description: Id or name of the move battle style

api_list.name: getMoveByName
api_list.description: Moves are the skills of Pokémon in battle. In battle, a Pokémon uses one move each turn. Some moves (including those learned by Hidden Machine) can be used outside of battle as well, usually for the purpose of removing obstacles or exploring new areas.

required_parameters.name: moveName
required_parameters.description: Id or name of the move

api_list.name: getMoveCategoryByName
api_list.description: Very general categories that loosely group move effects.

required_parameters.name: moveCategoryName
required_parameters.description: Id or name of the move category

api_list.name: getMoveDamageClassByName
api_list.description: Damage classes moves can have, e.g. physical, special, or non-damaging.

required_parameters.name: moveDamageClassName
required_parameters.description: Id or name of the move damage class

api_list.name: getMoveLearnMethodByName
api_list.description: Methods by which Pokémon can learn moves.

required_parameters.name: moveLearnMethodName
required_parameters.description: Id or name of the move learn method

api_list.name: getMoveTargetByName
api_list.description: Targets moves can be directed at during battle. Targets can be Pokémon, environments or even other moves.

required_parameters.name: moveTargetName
required_parameters.description: Id or name of the move target

api_list.name: getNatureByName
api_list.description: Natures influence how a Pokémon's stats grow.

required_parameters.name: natureName
required_parameters.description: Id or name of the nature

api_list.name: getPalParkAreaByName
api_list.description: Areas used for grouping Pokémon encounters in Pal Park. They're like habitats that are specific to Pal Park.

required_parameters.name: palParkAreaName
required_parameters.description: Id or name of the Pal Park area

api_list.name: getPokeathlonStatByName
api_list.description: Pokeathlon Stats are different attributes of a Pokémon's performance in Pokéathlons. In Pokéathlons, competitions happen on different courses; one for each of the different Pokéathlon stats.

required_parameters.name: pokeathlonStatName
required_parameters.description: Id or name of the pokeathlon stat

api_list.name: getPokedexByName
api_list.description: A Pokédex is a handheld electronic encyclopedia device; one which is capable of recording and retaining information of the various Pokémon in a given region with the exception of the national dex and some smaller dexes related to portions of a region.

required_parameters.name: pokedexName
required_parameters.description: Id or name of the pokedex

api_list.name: getPokemonByName
api_list.description: Pokémon are the creatures that inhabit the world of the Pokémon games. They can be caught using Pokéballs and trained by battling with other Pokémon.

required_parameters.name: pokemonName
required_parameters.description: Id or name of the pokemon

api_list.name: getPokemonColorByName
api_list.description: Colors used for sorting Pokémon in a Pokédex. The color listed in the Pokédex is usually the color most apparent or covering each Pokémon's body. No orange category exists; Pokémon that are primarily orange are listed as red or brown.

required_parameters.name: pokemonColorName
required_parameters.description: Id or name of the pokemon color

api_list.name: getPokemonFormByName
api_list.description: Some Pokémon have the ability to take on different forms. At times, these differences are purely cosmetic and have no bearing on the difference in the Pokémon's stats from another; however, several Pokémon differ in stats (other than HP), type, and Ability depending on their form.

required_parameters.name: pokemonFormName
required_parameters.description: Id or name of the pokemon form

api_list.name: getPokemonHabitatByName
api_list.description: Habitats are generally different terrain Pokémon can be found in but can also be areas designated for rare or legendary Pokémon.

required_parameters.name: pokemonHabitatName
required_parameters.description: Id or name of the pokemon habitat

api_list.name: getPokemonShapeByName
api_list.description: Shapes used for sorting Pokémon in a Pokédex.

required_parameters.name: pokemonShapeName
required_parameters.description: Id or name of the pokemon shape

api_list.name: getPokemonSpeciesByName
api_list.description: A Pokémon Species forms the basis for at least one Pokémon. Attributes of a Pokémon species are shared across all varieties of Pokémon within the species. A good example is Wormadam; Wormadam is the species which can be found in three different varieties, Wormadam-Trash, Wormadam-Sandy and Wormadam-Plant.

required_parameters.name: pokemonSpeciesName
required_parameters.description: Id or name of the pokemon species

api_list.name: getRegionByName
api_list.description: A region is an organized area of the Pokémon world. Most often, the main difference between regions is the species of Pokémon that can be encountered within them.

required_parameters.name: regionName
required_parameters.description: Id or name of the region

api_list.name: getStatByName
api_list.description: Stats determine certain aspects of battles. Each Pokémon has a value for each stat which grows as they gain levels and can be altered momentarily by effects in battles.

required_parameters.name: statName
required_parameters.description: Id or name of the stat

api_list.name: getSuperContestEffectById
api_list.description: Returns super contest effect according to provided Id

required_parameters.name: contestId
required_parameters.description: Id of the contest type

api_list.name: getTypeByName
api_list.description: Types are properties for Pokémon and their moves. Each type has three properties: which types of Pokémon it is super effective against, which types of Pokémon it is not very effective against, and which types of Pokémon it is completely ineffective against.

required_parameters.name: typeName
required_parameters.description: Id or name of the type

api_list.name: getVersionByName
api_list.description: Versions of the games, e.g., Red, Blue or Yellow.

required_parameters.name: versionName
required_parameters.description: Id or name of the version

api_list.name: getVersionGroupByName
api_list.description: Version groups categorize highly similar versions of the games.

required_parameters.name: versionGroupName
required_parameters.description: Id or name of the version group
